<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="290" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[150,1436,352,583]" pageId="1" pageNumber="290">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,316,386,409]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="290" reason="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This genus can be distinguished from the other members of the family by: long and slender legs I, II and IV; long and flexible tarsi (this character also occurs in 
<taxonomicName authority="Davies &amp; Raven, 1980" authorityName="Davies &amp; Raven" authorityYear="1980" box="[757,1190,421,444]" class="Arachnida" family="Pisauridae" genus="Megadolomedes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[757,932,421,444]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="290">Megadolomedes</emphasis>
Davies &amp; Raven, 1980
</taxonomicName>
, endemic to 
<collectingCountry box="[1329,1428,421,444]" name="Australia" pageId="1" pageNumber="290">Australia</collectingCountry>
) (Fig. 24); distal tegular apophysis membranous, conductor membranous (
<figureCitation box="[930,999,456,479]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–9" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1931,1954]" captionTargetBox="[285,1311,194,1895]" captionTargetId="figure-64@3.[285,1311,194,1895]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7–9. Hygropoda tangana (Roewer, 1955) comb. nov. 7, 8 left male palpus (7 ventral, 8 retrolateral). 9 female epigynum (ventral). (BPT = basal projection of tegulum, C = conductor, DTA = distal tegular apophysis, E = embolus, MA = median apophysis, RTA = retrolateral tibial apophysis, ST = subtegulum)." pageId="1" pageNumber="290">Figs 7</figureCitation>
, 26), large and sclerotized embolus (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 10–13" captionStartId="4.[151,269,1938,1961]" captionTargetBox="[204,1373,194,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-72@4.[204,1373,194,1908]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–13. Hygropoda tangana (Roewer, 1955) comb. nov. 10–13 left male palpus (10 ventral, 11 details of bulb, 12 retrolateral, 13 detail of retrolateral tibial apophysis). (BPT = basal projection of tegulum, C = conductor, DTA = distal tegular apophysis, E = embolus, MA = median apophysis, RTA = retrolateral tibial apophysis, ST = subtegulum)." pageId="1" pageNumber="290">Figs 11</figureCitation>
, 30). The females present a short and rounded spermatheca (
<figureCitation box="[820,896,490,513]" captionStart="FIGURES 14–19" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1540,1563]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,194,1516]" captionTargetId="figure-151@5.[151,1436,194,1516]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 14–19. Hygropoda tangana (Roewer, 1955) comb. nov. 14–17 female epigynum (14 ventral, without copulatory plug, 15 ventral, with copulatory plug, 16 dorsal, 17 detail of the head of spermathecae, dorsal view). 18 trichobothria of right leg IV, 19 tarsal claw of left leg II, prolateral view. (BS = base of spermathecae, CD = copulatory duct, CP = copulatory plug, FD = fertilization duct, HS = head of spermathecae, LL = lateral lobes, MF = middle field of epigynum)." pageId="1" pageNumber="290">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
) and base of spermatheca and copulatory ducts are enlarged and curved (
<figureCitation box="[381,461,525,548]" captionStart="FIGURES 14–19" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1540,1563]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,194,1516]" captionTargetId="figure-151@5.[151,1436,194,1516]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 14–19. Hygropoda tangana (Roewer, 1955) comb. nov. 14–17 female epigynum (14 ventral, without copulatory plug, 15 ventral, with copulatory plug, 16 dorsal, 17 detail of the head of spermathecae, dorsal view). 18 trichobothria of right leg IV, 19 tarsal claw of left leg II, prolateral view. (BS = base of spermathecae, CD = copulatory duct, CP = copulatory plug, FD = fertilization duct, HS = head of spermathecae, LL = lateral lobes, MF = middle field of epigynum)." pageId="1" pageNumber="290">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
